The paper deals with linear dimensionality reduction and norm preservation, which are common topics in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of sparse random matrices also suggests a connection to compressed sensing (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper presents a unified framework that encompasses several existing results, which could be seen as a contribution to the theory of algorithms (cs.SI).
